                         446 --192: /**
                         447 --193: *************************************************************************************
                         448 --194: **
                         449 --195: **   Shut down the Drome subsystem. \n
                         450 --196: **
                         451 --197: **   This function shall be used by the application prior to turning the power
                         452 --198: **   off. The purpose is to put Drome in a safe state and make sure no damage
                         453 --199: **   comes to the hardware, e.g. by shutting down the power to the TFT display in
                         454 --200: **   an orderly fashion. \n
                         455 --201: **

                                                                      Page 9
                                                              C:\Users\minda\AppData\Local\Temp\gh_000031s1.si
                         456 --202: **   When it's time to shut down the system, this function shall be called
                         457 --203: **   repeatedly until it returns TRUE. During this time, no other "drome_" requests
                         458 --204: **   shall be made. Once drome_shutDown() has been called, Drome and related
                         459 --205: **   hardware drivers must be reinitialized to make Drome operate again.
                         460 --206: **
                         461 --207: **    \return  TRUE  - Shut-down complete. \n
                         462 --208: **             FALSE - Shut-down in progress, call again later.
                         463 --209: **
                         464 --210: **************************************************************************************
                         465 --211: **/
