                        1450 --549: /**
                        1451 --550:  *************************************************************************************
                        1452 --551:  **
                        1453 --552:  **   Draws a view with a given key. This is i.e. a popup ,debug view or a view named 
                        1454 --553:  **   X_nnnn_Name in the guide model. The X & nnnn will be the key for this function. 
                        1455 --554:  **
                        1456 --555:  **   After making a successful call to this function, the application has the control 
                        1457 --556:  **   over the view displayed on screen. The state machine will keep updating its current 
                        1458 --557:  **   view but this view will only be drawn after calling the interface
                        1459 --558:  **   drome_returnViewControlToStateMachine().
                        1460 --559:  **
                        1461 --560:  **   NOTE! \n
                        1462 --561:  **   If the view was not found, a default error view is displayed, specifying what view
                        1463 --562:  **   was requested but not found.
                        1464 --563:  **
                        1465 --564:  **   \return  TRUE    View existed and was set to be drawn. \n
                        1466 --565:  **            FALSE   View did not exist, error view will be drawn. 
                        1467 --566:  **
