                        1564 --595: /**
                        1565 --596:  *************************************************************************************
                        1566 --597:  **
                        1567 --598:  **   This function is used by the application to tell drome to redraw the currently 
                        1568 --599:  **   active view. The reason for redrawing could be that the whole screen shall be 
                        1569 --600:  **   redrawn with some interval, or that some global properties controlling the 
                        1570 --601:  **   view has changed. Physical redrawing will start on the next cyclic sent to drome.
                        1571 --602:  **
                        1572 --603:  **   Calls to this function will tell drome to redraw the current view. Actual
                        1573 --604:  **   redrawing will start on the next cyclic call.
                        1574 --605:  **
                        1575 --606:  **   WARNING! \n
                        1576 --607:  **   If a view was currently drawing, this call will abort that drawing!
                        1577 --608:  **   
                        1578 --609:  **    \return  TRUE    If the view was possible to setup for a redraw. \n
                        1579 --610:  **             FALSE   If last redrawView() command was not completed.
